index.html.title: DjipAV
index.html.name: DjipAV
index.html.summary: A library to simplify working with audio and video inputs (a.k.a. webcams and microphones) on the web

AudioMeter.html.title: AudioMeter
AudioMeter.html.name: AudioMeter
AudioMeter.html.description: The AudioMeter class analyzes audio an input and reports on its level (volume). It can be used in a WebAudio chain by connecting a source node to its input property: let am = new AudioMeter(context); someSourceAudioNode.connect(am.input);

VideoInput.html.title: VideoInput
VideoInput.html.name: VideoInput
VideoInput.html.description: Creates a new VideoInput object and attaches it to the specified <video> element for viewing. If no <video> element is specified, the stream will not be visible. If the special value "create" is used, a new <video> element is created and appended to the <body>. A reference to the video element is accessible via the video property. By default, the first video input track will be used. To find a specific video input, a MediaTrackConstraints must be specified in the constraints parameter.

VideoInput.html#capabilities.title: capabilities :MediaTrackCapabilities
VideoInput.html#capabilities.name: capabilities
VideoInput.html#capabilities.description: A MediaTrackCapabilities object detailing the exact capabilities of the video track (or null if no video track is currently open).

VideoInput.html#capture.title: capture :ImageCapture
VideoInput.html#capture.name: capture
VideoInput.html#capture.description: An ImageCapture object used to grab frames per the ImageCapture API.

VideoInput.html#constraints.title: constraints :MediaTrackConstraints
VideoInput.html#constraints.name: constraints
VideoInput.html#constraints.description: The constraints which must be met by the video track. At the minimum, the value true is used which means all input video streams.

VideoInput.html#opacity.title: opacity :number
VideoInput.html#opacity.name: opacity
VideoInput.html#opacity.description: The opacity of the <video> element used to display the video stream (between 0 and 1).

VideoInput.html#settings.title: settings :MediaTrackSettings
VideoInput.html#settings.name: settings
VideoInput.html#settings.description: A MediaTrackSettings object detailing the precise settings of the video track (or null if no stream is open).

VideoInput.html#started.title: started :boolean
VideoInput.html#started.name: started
VideoInput.html#started.description: Whether or not the video input is currently started.

VideoInput.html#stream.title: stream :MediaStream
VideoInput.html#stream.name: stream
VideoInput.html#stream.description: The actual media stream that is currently being used.

VideoInput.html#timeouts.title: timeouts :Object
VideoInput.html#timeouts.name: timeouts
VideoInput.html#timeouts.description: An object containing the timeouts used throughout this class (mostly for internal use)

VideoInput.html#track.title: track :MediaStreamTrack
VideoInput.html#track.name: track
VideoInput.html#track.description: The video track currently being used. This will be null if there are no active stream.

VideoInput.html#video.title: video :HTMLMediaElement
VideoInput.html#video.name: video
VideoInput.html#video.description: The <video> element used to display the video feed (may be null if none is used)

VideoInput.html#cancelFade.title: cancelFade()
VideoInput.html#cancelFade.name: cancelFade
VideoInput.html#cancelFade.description: Cancels any fade ins or fade outs that are currently ongoing.

VideoInput.html#destroy.title: <async> destroy() → {Promise.<void>}
VideoInput.html#destroy.name: destroy
VideoInput.html#destroy.description: Properly destroys this object and all internal references. By calling this method when you are done with this object, you insure there are no lingering listeners or processes.

VideoInput.html#fade.title: <async> fade( [ type [, duration ] ] ) → {Promise.<void>}
VideoInput.html#fade.name: fade
VideoInput.html#fade.description: Fades the <video> element in or out for the specified duration.

VideoInput.html#fadeIn.title: <async> fadeIn( [ duration ] ) → {Promise.<void>}
VideoInput.html#fadeIn.name: fadeIn
VideoInput.html#fadeIn.description: Fades in the <video> element used to display the video feed.

VideoInput.html#fadeOut.title: <async> fadeOut( [ duration ] ) → {Promise.<void>}
VideoInput.html#fadeOut.name: fadeOut
VideoInput.html#fadeOut.description: Fades out the <video> element used to display the video feed.

VideoInput.html#grabFrame.title: <async> grabFrame( [ options ] ) → {Promise.<(ImageBitmap|DOMString|Blob)>}
VideoInput.html#grabFrame.name: grabFrame
VideoInput.html#grabFrame.description: Grabs a frame from the video stream and returns it in the specified data format.

VideoInput.html#start.title: <async> start( [ options ] ) → {Promise.<void>}
VideoInput.html#start.name: start
VideoInput.html#start.description: Tries to find a video stream matching the specified constraints. If one is found, the stream is attached to the <video> element specified upon construction of the VideoInput object (if any).

VideoInput.html#stop.title: <async> stop() → {Promise.<void>}
VideoInput.html#stop.name: stop
VideoInput.html#stop.description: Disconnects the video input and stops all associated tracks.
